COPS in Vhalaudzi outside Thohoyandou are requesting the
community to help in locating a 29-year-old missing person, Lutendo Malibana of
Mazuwa village. Cops spokesperson constable Mienkie Ramakgoakgoa said it
is alleged that the missing man was last seen on 22 August, after he left home
to a nearby mountain. She said the police were notified and a search operation ensued
at the nearest mountains and the surrounding areas, but he was nowhere to be
found. Anyone with information about the whereabouts of this
missing person, may contact Warrant Officer Tharaga at 076 646 1987 or the
nearest Police Station or the Crime Stop number 08600 10111 or the crime line
sms 32211. 